                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>During the morning of December 16 Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName> discussed the Trieste question with Italian Prime
                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_PELLAG1">Pella</persName> for three quarters of
                    an hour. In setting up the meeting Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName> had told <persName corresp="#p_PELLAG1">Pella</persName>
                    that he was unwilling to go into details on the subject or negotiate about it.
                    The United States Delegation reported the substance of the discussion in
                    telegram 2319 from Paris, December 16, which is printed in the compilation on
                    Trieste in volume VIII.</p>
            </div>
